==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Toward
<hw>To"ward</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS. <?/. See
<er>Toward</er>, <pos>prep.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Approaching;
coming near.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧His <xex>toward</xex> peril.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Readly to do or learn; compliant with duty; not
froward; apt; docile; tractable; <as>as, a <ex>toward</ex>
youth</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Ready to act; forward; bold; valiant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Why, that is spoken like a <qex>toward</qex> prince.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Towardliness</ent>⟦br⟧
